<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68fe464-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s11110"><num value="11110">§ 11110.</num><heading> Seamen’s clothing</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The clothing of a seaman is exempt from attachments and liens. A person detaining a seaman’s clothing shall be fined not more than $500, imprisoned for not more than 6 months, or both.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf68fe465-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/580">97 Stat. 580</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
